properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 15 at 3:09PM PST until January 16 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, east to southeast winds 15
to 25 kt. For the Gale Warning, south winds 25 to 35 kt.

* WHERE...Puget Sound and Hood Canal.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 4 PM PST this
afternoon. For the Gale Warning, until 4 AM PST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST THURSDAY
